In [2]:
for i in range(3, 6):
    # URL of the page to scrape
    url = "https://www.basketball-reference.com/leagues/NBA_202"+str(i)+".html"
    # Send a GET request to the URL
    response = requests.get(url)
    # Parse the HTML content of the page
    soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser')
    tables = soup.find_all('table', id="per_poss-team")
    for table in tables:
        # Find the table header
        header = table.find('thead')
        # Find the table body
        body = table.find('tbody')
        # Extract the column names from the header
        columns = [th.get_text() for th in header.find_all('th')]
        # Extract the data from the body
        data = []
        for row in body.find_all('tr'):
            row_data = [td.get_text() for td in row.find_all('td')]
            if row_data:  # Only add non-empty rows
                data.append(row_data)
                
        # Create a DataFrame from the extracted data
        df = pd.DataFrame(data, columns=columns[1:])  # Exclude the first column (index)
        df['rk'] = range(1, len(df) + 1)  # Add a rank column
        # Convert the 'rk' column to numeric
        df['rk'] = pd.to_numeric(df['rk'], errors='coerce')
        df['Playoffs'] = np.where(df['Team'].str.contains(r'\*'), 1, 0)
        # Drop games played
        df = df.drop(columns=['G'])
        # Drop minutes played
        df = df.drop(columns=['MP'])
        df.to_csv("team_stats_202"+str(i)+".csv", index=False)

# Read the CSV files into DataFrames
dataframes = []
for i in range(3, 6):
    # Read the CSV file into a DataFrame
    df = pd.read_csv("team_stats_202"+str(i)+".csv")
    # Add a new column for the year
    df['Year'] = 2020 + i
    # Append the DataFrame to the list
    dataframes.append(df)

Summary of Each Feature: FG(Field Goals),FGA(Field Goal Attempts),3P(3 Pointers),3P% (3 Point percentage),FT(Free throws),FT%(Free throw Percentage) ORB(Offensive Rebound),DRB(Defensive Rebounds),TRB(Total Rebounds),AST(Assists),STL(Steals),BLK(Blocks),TOV(Turnovers),PF(Personal Fouls)

# Visualize the data based on 3 pointers made with Playoffs as the color
custom_palette = {0: 'blue', 1: 'green'}
for data in dataframes:
    ax1 = sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='rk', y='3P', hue='Playoffs', palette=custom_palette, style='Playoffs')

handles, labels = ax1.get_legend_handles_labels()

# Extract the handles and labels for the style legend
markers = [0, 1]  # Playoffs: 0 for no, 1 for yes
style_handles = []
style_labels = []
seen_styles = set()
for handle, label in zip(handles, labels):
    if label in [str(val) for val in markers] and label not in seen_styles:
        style_handles.append(handle)
        style_labels.append(label)
        seen_styles.add(label)

# Create the style-only legend
style_labels = ['No Playoffs', 'Playoffs']
plt.legend(style_handles, style_labels, title='Category', loc='upper right')
plt.title('3 Pointers Made by Rank Across Three Years')
plt.xlabel('Rank')
plt.ylabel('3 Pointers Made per 100 Possessions')
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

# Removing highly correlated features
def remove_highly_correlated_features(df, threshold=0.8):
    # Calculate the correlation matrix
    corr_matrix = df.corr().abs()
    # Select upper triangle of correlation matrix
    upper = corr_matrix.where(np.triu(np.ones(corr_matrix.shape), k=1).astype(bool))
    # Find index of feature columns with correlation greater than the threshold
    to_drop = [column for column in upper.columns if any(upper[column] > threshold)]
    # Drop the features
    df.drop(columns=to_drop, inplace=True)
    return df

# Apply the function to combine DataFrames
df = pd.concat(dataframes)
Y = df['Playoffs']
# Remove highly correlated features
df = remove_highly_correlated_features(df.drop(columns=['rk', 'Playoffs', 'Team']), threshold=0.8)
# Put into new csv
df.to_csv("team_stats_2023_2025.csv", index=False)

# Correlation matrix After removing highly correlated features

# Plot the correlation matrix

plt.title('Correlation Matrix of Team Stats (2023-2025)')

In [ ]:
# Let's try a Random Forest Classifier
clf = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, random_state=42)
X = df
# Split the data into training and testing sets
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, Y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)
# Fit the model
clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
# Make predictions
y_pred = clf.predict(X_test)
# Calculate the accuracy
accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)

print(f"Accuracy: {accuracy:.2f}")
# Print the classification report
print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))

# Print the confusion matrix
cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', xticklabels=['No Playoffs', 'Playoffs'], yticklabels=['No Playoffs', 'Playoffs'])
plt.title('Confusion Matrix')

# XGBoost Classifier
xgb_clf = XGBClassifier(use_label_encoder=False, eval_metric='logloss')

param_grid = {
    'max_depth': [3, 5, 7],
    'learning_rate': [0.01, 0.1, 0.2],
    'n_estimators': [50, 100, 150],
    'subsample': [0.7, 1.0],
    'colsample_bytree': [0.7, 1.0]
}
grid_search = GridSearchCV(estimator=xgb_clf, param_grid=param_grid, 
                           scoring='accuracy', cv=3, verbose=1, n_jobs=-1)

# Fit the model
grid_search.fit(X_train, y_train)
xgb_clf = grid_search.best_estimator_
# Make predictions
y_pred_xgb = xgb_clf.predict(X_test)
# Calculate the accuracy
accuracy_xgb = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_xgb)
print(f"XGBoost Accuracy: {accuracy_xgb:.2f}")
# Print the classification report
print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred_xgb))
# Print the confusion matrix
cm_xgb = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_xgb)
plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))
sns.heatmap(cm_xgb, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', xticklabels=['No Playoffs', 'Playoffs'], yticklabels=['No Playoffs', 'Playoffs'])
plt.title('XGBoost Confusion Matrix')

class SimpleNN(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, input_size):
        super(SimpleNN, self).__init__()
        # Define 4 layer Neural Network with ReLU activations
        # and Sigmoid activation for the output layer
        self.layer1 = nn.Linear(input_size, 64)
        self.relu = nn.ReLU()
        self.layer2 = nn.Linear(64, 32)
        self.relu2 = nn.ReLU()
        self.layer3 = nn.Linear(32, 1)
        self.sigmoid = nn.Sigmoid()

    def forward(self, x):
        x = self.relu(self.layer1(x))
        x = self.relu2(self.layer2(x))
        x = self.sigmoid(self.layer3(x))
        return x

    def train_model(self, X_train, y_train, X_test, y_test, num_epochs=100, learning_rate=0.001, batch_size=32):
        # Define the loss function and optimizer
        criterion = nn.BCELoss()
        optimizer = torch.optim.Adam(self.parameters(), lr=learning_rate)

        # Training loop
        for epoch in range(num_epochs):
            for i in range(0, len(X_train), batch_size):
                # Get batch
                X_batch = X_train[i:i+batch_size]
                y_batch = y_train[i:i+batch_size]

                # Forward pass
                y_pred = self(X_batch)
                loss = criterion(y_pred, y_batch)

                # Backward pass and optimization
                optimizer.zero_grad()
                loss.backward()
                optimizer.step()

            # Print progress
            if (epoch+1) % 10 == 0:
                print(f'Epoch [{epoch+1}/{num_epochs}], Loss: {loss.item():.4f}')

        # Evaluate the model
        with torch.no_grad():
            y_pred_test = self(X_test)
            y_pred_class = (y_pred_test > 0.5).float()  # Threshold at 0.5 for classification
            accuracy = (y_pred_class == y_test).float().mean()
            print(f'Test Accuracy: {accuracy:.4f}')

scaler = StandardScaler()
#Convert data to tensors
X_train_scaled = torch.tensor(scaler.fit_transform(X_train), dtype=torch.float32)
X_test_scaled = torch.tensor(scaler.transform(X_test), dtype=torch.float32)
y_train_tensor = torch.tensor(y_train.values, dtype=torch.float32).view(-1, 1)
y_test_tensor = torch.tensor(y_test.values, dtype=torch.float32).view(-1, 1)
input_size = X_train_scaled.shape[1]
# Initialize the model
model = SimpleNN(input_size)
# Train the model
model.train_model(X_train_scaled, y_train_tensor, X_test_scaled, y_test_tensor, num_epochs=100, learning_rate=0.001, batch_size=32)
# Make predictions
with torch.no_grad():
    # Make predictions on the test set
    y_pred_test = model(X_test_scaled)
    # Convert predictions to class labels
    y_pred_class = (y_pred_test > 0.5).float()  # Threshold at 0.5
    # Calculate accuracy
    accuracy = (y_pred_class == y_test_tensor).float().mean()
    print(f'Test Accuracy: {accuracy:.4f}')
